  "overview_metadata": {
    "overview_number": 3,
    "overview_title": "The Elimination Round",
    "overview_subtitle": "Using Linear Combinations to Solve a System of Linear Equations",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students explore a system of equations with opposite <math><mi>y</mi></math>-coefficients and isolate <math><mi>x</mi></math> by adding the equations together. They learn the linear combinations method and analyze systems that they can solve by multiplying either one or both equations by a constant to rewrite the system with a single variable. They apply the linear combinations method to solve problems."
  },
