      "overview_item_data": {
        "overview_item_data_type": "list",
        "overview_item_data_items": [
          "The linear combinations method is a process to solve a system of linear equations by adding two equations together, resulting in an equation in one variable.",
          "When using linear combinations, it is often necessary to multiply one or both equations by a constant to create two equations in which the coefficients of one of the variables are additive inverses."
